John Nagle (nagle@netcom.com) wrote:
:      That's a problem.  Consider the possibility of a virus which 
: patches copies of your local crypto application to insert such a
: Trojan horse.
: 
:      It's this sort of threat that makes NSA insist that all DoD crypto
: be in dedicated, isolated, hardware.
: 
: 					John Nagle

Yes, in this example, the defense against PGP's being compromised in 
this manner is essentially its wide distribution on multiple independent
servers _before_ its existence became widely known.

Of course, it could _all_ be a giant conspiracy ;).

